subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (fig. 
25
). Pygofer with convex hind margin. Anal tube wide, flat, with notch apically. Phallobase flattened dorso-ventrally. Dorso-lateral phallobase lobes not fused apically. Each dorso-lateral phallobase lobe narrows apically, with lobe-shaped projection under aedeagal ventral hooks (in lateral view). Ventral phallobase lobe reaching apices of dorso-lateral lobes, broad, widely rounded apically with notch. Aedeagus with a pair of long ventral hooks. Apical aedegal processes long, protruding above apical margin of phallobase, narrow apically. Suspensorium well sclerotized. Style with convex hind margin, caudo-dorsal angle narrowly rounded. Capitulum of style flattened laterally, on short neck, with large lateral tooth situated perpendicular to capitulum.
